      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues] Line 98: The new congestion trigger inherits the previous EWMA initial value of 10%, so a first RTCP report with 0% loss computes `pondLoss_ \u003d 5` and immediately fires audio congestion because the threshold is 3%. That will reduce video bitrate on clean calls. Initialize the EWMA to 0 for the new congestion path, or avoid using the smoothed bootstrap value for congestion decisions.\n```suggestion\nfloat pondLoss_ {0.0f};\n```",
      "revId": "90a5e57694ebd64e7e072dda45579374cc3b248c",
