      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 52: The global simulator registry stores shared simulators indefinitely unless tests remember to call `clear()`/`removeAll()`. Because keys are arbitrary call IDs and the registry is process-global, integration tests can leak state across calls or test cases and produce order-dependent failures. Prefer RAII-scoped registration, weak entries, or ensure call teardown removes simulators consistently where the SocketPair/session is destroyed.",
      "revId": "90a5e57694ebd64e7e072dda45579374cc3b248c",
