      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 633: The simulator drops only outgoing RTP after SRTP/packetization, but `writeCallback()` returns `buf_size` as if the packet was sent. This makes sender-side statistics and backpressure believe transmission succeeded, while receiver-side RTCP reports loss later. That may be acceptable for a test-only fault injector, but this code is compiled into production media sources with no build/test guard and no public attachment path shown in this change. Gate this integration behind a test/debug build option or keep the simulator out of production code paths.",
      "revId": "90a5e57694ebd64e7e072dda45579374cc3b248c",
