      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 806: `onAudioCongestion()` reduces bitrate every cooldown interval even when video is already at the minimum, and it does not coordinate with the existing bitrate-decrease timers/counters. This can cause repeated encoder reconfiguration/log spam and interfere with normal REMB adaptation. Return early when `oldBitrate \u003c\u003d videoBitrateInfo_.videoBitrateMin`, and update/reuse the existing decrease state if this is meant to be part of congestion control.",
