      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 128: The jitter test is probabilistic and can flake: uniform jitter over 10 packets can legally produce a total sleep of 0ms or slightly exceed the arbitrary timing bound on loaded CI. Avoid asserting wall-clock randomness; inject a deterministic RNG/clock or test deterministic bounds with max jitter disabled/enabled through a controllable dependency.",
      "revId": "90a5e57694ebd64e7e072dda45579374cc3b248c",
